  "prompt": "What is Google Penguin?",
  "response": "Google Penguin is an algorithm update launched by Google in April 2012, aimed at reducing web spam and enhancing search engine results by targeting websites that violate Google's Webmaster Guidelines. Specifically, Penguin focuses on penalizing sites that engage in manipulative link-building practices or have an unnatural backlink profile. \n\nBefore the Penguin update, some websites were able to achieve high rankings by acquiring a large number of low-quality or spammy backlinks. The Penguin update sought to level the playing field by ensuring that only sites with genuine, high-quality backlinks would rank well. Subsequent updates and iterations of Google Penguin have been integrated into Google's core search algorithm, allowing for more real-time and continuous adjustments rather than periodic refreshes.",
